There was a time when I thought I was in love and miserable.<br>
Sitting by the phone waiting for him to call, wondering why he didn't. Waiting for him to show up, and he's late or doesn't show at all, with no call. Then I woke up, realizing that he had the control of the relationship. I saw that I had given myself away, and that there was only one side, his side, his rules, his way. What was I thinking?<br>
Love is a two way street. Love does not hurt, control, abuse, misuse, or make you do things you are not ready to do. Love is kind, feels good, is open, communicates, shares, reinforces, gives strength, protects, is honest, empowers.....and wears a condom!
